## HPAI H5N1 in Denmark since last meeting

## Source of infections

- Epidemiological investigations still ongoing, but most probably indirect contacts with wildbirds.
- All primary outbreaks

## In generel biosecurity ok

- But hobbyflocks, turkeys and gamebirds are not housed in very closed establishments

## Outbreak no 20: 98.800 layers with low level of biosecurity

- Poor maintenance, access for wild birds, pest control inadequate, garbage around the buildings, etc.
- possible police case

## Outbreak no 25: Hobbyflock with low level of biosecurity

- hens, geese, ducks, pheasants, pigeons, ornamental birds and different (pet) mammals
- -pigs, goats, dogs, cats, rabbits, guineapigs etc.
- No separation between species
- Mammals tested -all negative for HPAI

<!-- image -->

## HPAI H5N1 in Denmark 2025/2026 season -further measures

## Still high risk period

- national regulation in place since October 2025/indoor housing order
- feed and water under roof/indoor
- ducks and geese should be kept apart/no contact with other poultry
- ban of markets, exhibitions and other gatherings
- preventive vaccination in zoos

## Still focus on increased awareness/biosecurity

- Press releases, info at webpages, meetings with stakeholders, so-me etc.
- General info and info targeted at stakeholders:
- Biosecurity
- focus on clinical symptoms
- wild birds
- Weekly expert group meetings
- Epidemiological report for each outbreak

Campaign with extra control of biosecurity in poultry establishments with focus on hobby flocks is being planned

